riors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/20/03 1:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2793.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Question about windblade and aggro</span><hr size=1> My whole life ive heard that number of hits means more to aggro than DPS. So this is kinda making me wonder why is everyone using windblades, the windblade is great DPS weapon, however if number of hits is greater than DPS, wouldnt that make for bad aggro. I understand using one when your not MA, however I see people telling others just to get a windblade over good taunting 1h slash weapons while at their level they have plenty of exp grouping to go. Even with triple attack, your still hitting more duel wielding, and chances are hitting with a proc you wont get with the windblade. So basically why is everyone moving to windblade, I honestly dont get it hehe. I dont mean to be a troll or anything i just dont get it.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=keaneabrams>Keane Abrams</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/20/03 1:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2793.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question about windblade and aggro</span><hr size=1> I was using a 10 18 1hs crafted velium warsword and a Frosty then switched to the Windblade. The Windblade owns aggro compared to those two weaps. I regularly group with an epic monk and rogue and usually have no problems keeping aggro. <br>
<br>
Until I get an EB item, I will be using the Windblade. <p><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=174524"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.shatteredsword.com/sigs/keane.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 111<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/20/03 2:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2793.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question about windblade and aggro</span><hr size=1> More hits = more aggro but each hit have different amounts of aggro.  It's very easy to see that one hit from the 50/45 Windblade bothers a mob a lot more than one hit from a 10/18 weapon.  Each time you swing at the mob you generate some aggro as a function of the base damage of the weapon (and how hard and whether the hit actually lands has very little effect on the aggro generated).  So while your 10/18 can swing almost 3 times as fast as Windblade, each swing from Windblade might be worth 5 or even 6 of your swings.  The exact details of how much aggro is generated by the weapon base damage is unknown but not counting procs, 2Handers certainly generate a competitive amount of aggro via swinging compared to similar 1H combinations.   <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=wubaogoldenarmz>Wubao Goldenarmz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 375<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/20/03 8:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2793.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   mudflation at its finest</span><hr size=1> The difference in DPS between your AVERAGE pre-EB weapons that your AVERAGE warriors have access to (thinking Frosty + Whatever combo here) and a Windblade is rather LARGE.<br>
<br>
Windblade's DPS is quite a huge boost than what most warriors were using Pre-POP. So the Windblade holds aggro so much better because of the DPS being so much better.<br>
<br>
Least that's my theory and I'm sticking to it.<br>
<br>
:-)<br>
Wu <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=raunstoncutter>RaunStoncutter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 302<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/20/03 9:32 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2793.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/raunstonecutter/bunnyhop.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: mudflation at its finest</span><hr size=1> When the windblade gets going, its devistating for agro.<br>
<br>
Tonight in HoT, I was tanking with my 1h set up, but I would still lose agro sometimes to folks with windblades.  A good triple for 900 really pisses mobs off =)<br>
<br>
It depends on the situtaion and your RNG luck (mine sucks), but typically, I don't have problems holding agro with the windblade. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=31658">Raun Stonecutter</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.swordoffate.com">&lt;Sword of Fate&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=124485">Deterious</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.swordoffate.com">&lt;Sword of Fate&gt;</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=waledorwarblayde>Waledor Warblayde</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/20/03 10:10 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2793.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.bestanimations.com/Fantasy/Fantasy-01.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: mudflation at its finest</span><hr size=1> I just switched from a Wavecrasher / Frosty combo. Even with high dex and high procs from both, Windblade is holding alot better aggro. Only lost aggro few times in HoT (nukers overcasting) and almost never in XP groups. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-family:engravers MT;font-size:small;">Waledor Warblayde</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:red;font-family:engravers MT;font-size:x-small;">61 Warlord</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:blue;font-family:engravers MT;font-size:small;">Co-Leader of The Gathered</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=215887" target="top">Inspect me at your own risk-- Magelo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=phantron>Phantron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 112<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/20/03 11:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2793.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question about windblade and aggro</span><hr size=1> My theory is that each swing you make at the mob, the aggro is modified by plus or minus some random %.  I know aggro is not damage dependent (or at least depends very weakly) because /disc defensive and attack debuff does not make aggro harder despite a considerable lost of DPS in both cases.  So with 2H, it's possible to get a bad streak of bad random modifiers and lose aggro (which would also explain why sometimes you'd see someone using 2H suddenly getting aggro but then never again) but over the long run, it should work out to be a reliable source of aggro.  <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bumbleroot>Bumbleroot</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 66<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/21/03 5:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2793.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question about windblade and aggro</span><hr size=1> I bought a windblade simply to use when I'm not main tanking. However, as I would get on the backside of the mob, it quickly became apparent that I was pulling aggro easily without hitting the taunt button.<br>
Other two handers haven't posed this problem for me. I have in the past day gotten complaints from a druid for &quot;deciding to tank the mobs&quot; over our main tank. I also have gotten complaints from rogues who wish for me to get on the same side as the main tank. I never got those complaints until I bought my windblade.<br>
The windblade is doing a tremendous job in keeping aggro. So much so that I have considered breaking out my Grodan's Strength simply to have an aggro avoiding weapon in my arsenal. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daxos92>Daxos92</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 113<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/22/03 5:05 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2793.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question about windblade and aggro</span><hr size=1> As long as there is a shaman around to focus me, I still get better results with my Wavecrasher / Frosty combo for aggro, but not by all that much. Windblade is pretty slick dps (around 90 for me), and pre-EB that's tough to beat. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=443380" target="_blank">Daxos Valdorn</a><br>
Overlord of <a href="http://www.final-destiny.org" target="_blank">Final Destiny</a><br>
Ayonae Ro<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=valhalantrueblade>Valhalan Trueblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/22/03 8:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2793.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_pp.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Question about windblade and aggro</span><hr size=1> I think what your looking at here is very situational. <br>
<br>
I use Frosty/Ornate Sword of the General for my dual wield aggro setup.<br>
<br>
I have a Windblade for 2h.<br>
<br>
In most fights I have no problem maintaining aggro with my dual setup. Frosty proc's left and right! If I do lose it, a simple taunt, in most cases gets it back.<br>
<br>
Windblade, I have no problem maintaining aggro unless I go on a bad streak of misses. <br>
<br>
Now, Let me explain why this is situational:<br>
<br>
Recently I engaged in a a 30 minute battle in Katta against Nathyn Illuminious. <br>
<br>
This guy has a ton of HP and High Mitigation. I started the fight with my dual wield setup. Did not lose aggro once! About 1/2 way through the fight, I switched to Windblade. The DPS on it was horrible. His mitigation was too high for it to be effective. While I maintained aggro for most of the fight, near the end, the Monk was pulling aggro off me.<br>
<br>
So, as you can see, in High Mitigation fights, using a Windblade would not be effective enough to maintain aggro. <br>
<br>
Valhalan Trueblade<br>
Barbarian Warlord of Rallos Zek<br>
Bristlebane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kyryll>Kyryll</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/22/03 10:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2793.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_pp.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Question about windblade and aggro</span><hr size=1> I totally agree with Valhalan.<br>
<br>
I don't have a Windblade, but I DO have a Shovel of the Harvest (50/43 2hb). I can maintain agro with the shovel much better than my 1hs, 1hb, or pierce combos. The only time I switch out any more is for those high mitigation mobs, where it's advantageous to at least HIT the darn thing.<br>
<br>
