<br>
At level 65, the damage bonus of a 2H is roughly slightly greater than the delay.  If you assume you land exactly one swing per weapon round, that means you get roughly 10 DPS from damage bonus alone (ignoring haste since those scale the same both ways).<br>
<br>
At level 65, the damage bonus of a 1H is always 13 and the fastest weapons I know of are delay 18.  This translates to 7.22 DPS by the same criteria.  We'll be generous and call your offhand 1 DPS by the same measure (it's actually less than that), so you get 8.22 DPS.<br>
<br>
I repeat, mitigation has nothing to do with aggro.  There has never been any reported difficulty holding aggro on Xerzikh the Creator even though during the Luclin era you're pretty much looking at a min hit every swing mob.  Defensive does not make you lose half of your aggro even though it definitely makes you lose half of your DPS.  The mob is not very concerned with how hard you can actually hit it for (the damage) but how hard you ought to be able to hit it (the base weapon damage). <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=468916">Phantron</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=teldarr>Teldarr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/25/03 7:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2793.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Frostreaver</span><hr size=1> I always assumed 1hs was better aggro as well.  I had used a Windblade before but have never owned one.  However, I recently won a Frostreaver (42/43 and some stats + 125dd 0.0 sec stun proc).  A week or two later I won Dagarn's Tail from ntov (12/19 +10str +75hp +20svf. 51dd proc) and used it with The Horn of Hsagra (13/20 +10sta +75hp +25svc).<br>
